  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2985024049" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2985024049" />
    <a title="Pamela" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/30071749-pamela"><img alt="Pamela" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1509728263p2/30071749.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2985024049?book_show_action=true">Jul 03, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Pamela" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Pamela" href="/user/show/30071749-pamela">Pamela</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback " href="/book/show/18000059-mary-queen-of-scotland-and-the-isles">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/30071749-pamela?shelf=challenge-2021-classics-buffet">challenge-2021-classics-buffet</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/30071749-pamela?shelf=challenge-2021-classics-bingo">challenge-2021-classics-bingo</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2985024049" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15330871113101429223">Like Hilary Mantel with her Cromwell trilogy, Margaret George takes the real historical events of the life of Mary Stuart and imbues them with her imaginative view of how and why these events unrolled, creating thoughts and dialogues to flesh out the factual details. This gives rise to a very readable and engaging story, and creates an impression of Mary the person, alongside Mary as the dangerous political and religious symbol that inflamed her supporters and opponents.<br/><br/>George very skilfully sho</span>
  <span id="freeText15330871113101429223" style="display:none">Like Hilary Mantel with her Cromwell trilogy, Margaret George takes the real historical events of the life of Mary Stuart and imbues them with her imaginative view of how and why these events unrolled, creating thoughts and dialogues to flesh out the factual details. This gives rise to a very readable and engaging story, and creates an impression of Mary the person, alongside Mary as the dangerous political and religious symbol that inflamed her supporters and opponents.<br /><br />George very skilfully shows the complex political and religious situation in 16th century Europe and how this drives the actions of the main figures in Scotland, France and England. Mary is seen as impulsive and rather naive, trusting in the loyalty inspired by personal relationships and her idea of justice, and no match for the more cynical machinations of the Scottish lords and the advisers of Elizabeth I.<br /><br />This tragic story is initially full of excitement and danger, as Mary reels from one crisis to another (political, religious, romantic) and manages to escape from imprisonment, before finding herself at last isolated and lonely as the leaders of Europe abandon her cause and use her and her infant son James as a pawn in their treaty negotiations. The final section dealing with those wasted years are truly poignant and sad. <br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="15330871113101429223" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review2985024049">
  <td colspan="2">
