    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_64865122" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/64865122" />
    <a title="Sara Giacalone" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2548242-sara-giacalone"><img alt="Sara Giacalone" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1267897867p2/2548242.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/64865122?book_show_action=true">Jul 24, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sara Giacalone" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sara Giacalone" href="/user/show/2548242-sara-giacalone">Sara Giacalone</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer64865122" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10836559971275705716">I&apos;ve had this book for years and for the life of me can&apos;t figure out why it took me so long to read it, especially as I enjoyed &quot;The Autobiography of Henry VIII&quot;. Once I cracked it open, it took me no time to become hooked and I really enjoyed Margaret George&apos;s interpretation of Mary Queen of Scotland. After reading numerous factual books about the time period and the events, it was satisfying to read a more intimate, emotional portrayal of her life and times. Yes, the book is a bit long and has</span>
  <span id="freeText10836559971275705716" style="display:none">I've had this book for years and for the life of me can't figure out why it took me so long to read it, especially as I enjoyed "The Autobiography of Henry VIII". Once I cracked it open, it took me no time to become hooked and I really enjoyed Margaret George's interpretation of Mary Queen of Scotland. After reading numerous factual books about the time period and the events, it was satisfying to read a more intimate, emotional portrayal of her life and times. Yes, the book is a bit long and has lots of historical detail; isn't that a description of a good historical novel? I admit the last third dragged a bit, but isn't that to be expected? Once Mary is imprisoned, the majority of the action in the story moves away from her, and much of her "action" is internalized. I especially enjoyed George's interpretation of Mary and Bothwell's relationship. I, too, like imagining that Mary had a brief period of blissful happiness before Darnley's murder. In all, a very enjoyable book; one that I will probably read again.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10836559971275705716" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


